div.div:
Pmod ACL2
custom driver
interface.
Two modes of
operation to
select one of,
plus soft reset.
Linked Mode
Measure Mode
64-bit output
containing four
16-bit measurements.
Current status register
value output also.

box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: left;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: nowrap;

div.div:
The Pmod ACL2 custom driver operates by booting the ADXL362 and waiting for a strobe on one for the two
possible operation mode INIT signals.
Upon receiving a pulse on the Linked Init, the driver places the ADXL362 in Linked Mode with thresholds for
activity and inactivity detection.
Upon receiving a pulse on the Linked Start, the driver operates in Linked Mode. Measurements are taken by
waiting on an interrupt on INT1 or INT2, where INT1 is mapped to Inactivity event and INt2 is mapped to
Activity event. The currently read value of the status register is also output, which indicates AWAKE,
INACTIVITY, ACTIVITY and can be used for other values. To exit Linked Mode, it is necessary to send a pulse
on the Reset ACL2 signal.
Upon receiving a pulse on the Measure Init, the driver places the ADXL362 in Measure Mode with DATA READY
triggering the interrupt on INT1.
Upon receiving a pulse on the Measure Start, the driver operates in Measure Mode. Measurements are
continuously taken from the ADXL362 at 100 Hz and input on the SPI bus. At this continuous rate, the
four 16-bit measure registers are output on the 3 Axis Temp port with a Data Valid pulse on the Data Valid
port. To exit Measure Mode, it is necessary to send a pulse on the Reset ACL2 signal.
Upon receiving a button depress on the button input, the corresponding threshold preset selector increments
from 0 to 9, back to 0, and sets a part of the 7-byte configuration value for the initialization of Linked Mode.
The next time a pulse is received on Linked Start, the Linked Mode will use the two new threshold preset group
values (threshold and timer preset per preset selector).
